{"title_page": "List of cities in Maharashtra", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2019}}\n{{cleanup|reason=unnecessary [[WP:OR]]|date=August 2015}}\n'''[[Maharashtra]]''' ({{IPAc-en|m|\u0251\u02d0|h|\u0259|\u02c8|r|\u0251\u02d0|\u0283|t|r|\u0259}} {{IPA-mr |m\u0259hara\u02d0\u0282\u0288r\u0259||Maharashtra.ogg}}), is a [[States and territories of India|state]] in the [[West India|western]] region of [[India]]. It is a [[List of states and union territories of India by population|second most populous]] state after [[Uttar Pradesh]] and [[List of states and territories of India by area|third largest state by area]] in India. Maharashtra is the wealthiest state in India, contributing 15% of the country's industrial output and 13.3% of its GDP (2006\u20132007 figures).<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.worldbank.org.in/WBSITE/EXTERNAL/COUNTRIES/SOUTHASIAEXT/INDIAEXTN/0,,contentMDK:20951183~pagePK:141137~piPK:141127~theSitePK:295584,00.html | location = India | title = Countries | publisher = World Bank | date =  | accessdate = 2008-10-31 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120213182416/http://www.worldbank.org.in/WBSITE/EXTERNAL/COUNTRIES/SOUTHASIAEXT/INDIAEXTN/0,,contentMDK:20951183~pagePK:141137~piPK:141127~theSitePK:295584,00.html | archive-date = 13 February 2012 | url-status = dead }}</ref>\n\nMaharashtra is bordered in the [[Arabian Sea]] to the west, [[Gujarat]] and the [[Union territory]] of [[Dadra and Nagar Haveli]] to the northwest, [[Madhya Pradesh]] to the north and northeast, [[Chhattisgarh]] to the east, [[Karnataka]] to the south, [[Telangana]] to the southeast and [[Goa]] to the southwest. The state covers an area of {{convert|307731|km2|sqmi|0|abbr=on}} or 9.84% of the total geographical area of India. [[Mumbai]], the capital city of the state, is India's largest city and the financial capital of the nation. [[Nagpur]] is the second  capital of the state. [[Marathi language|Marathi]] is the state's official language.\n\nMaharashtra is the world's [[List of country subdivisions by population|second most populous first-level administrative country sub-division]]. Were it a nation in its own right, Maharashtra would be the [[List of countries by population|world's tenth most populous country]] ahead of [[Mexico]]. There are 41000 villages and 378 urban centres in Maharashtra.{{cn|date=April 2019}}\n\n==List of metropolitan areas in Maharashtra==\n\n{{See also|List of metropolitan areas in India}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Rank\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Metropolitan area\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Urban planning authority\n! class=\"unsortable\"| State/Territory\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Population<br />(2011)\n! style=\"width:12%;\"| Area<br />(in km<sup>2</sup>)\n!\n|-\n|1\n| [[Mumbai Metropolitan Region]]\n| [[Mumbai Metropolitan Region Development Authority]]\n| [[Maharashtra]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|24,800,000<ref>{{cite web|title=MMR \u2013 Population and Employment|url=http://www.naredco.in/pdfs/sc-deshpande.pdf|website=National Real Estate Development Council|publisher=Ministry of Housing and Urban Poverty Alleviation|accessdate=21 March 2016|page=4}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|4,354.5<ref>{{cite web|title=About MMR|url=https://mmrda.maharashtra.gov.in/about-mmr|website=Mumbai Metropolitan Region Development Authority|accessdate=21 March 2016}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n|2\n| [[Pune Metropolitan Area|Pune Metropolitan Region]]\n| [[Pune Metropolitan Region Development Authority]]\n| [[Maharashtra]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|10,100,000<ref name=\"pmrda\">{{cite news|title=Expansion plans: PMRDA wants 800 villages within limits|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/cities/pune/pune-redrawn-now-largest-urban-unit-in-maharashtra/|accessdate=18 March 2016|work=The Indian Express|date=8 December 2015|location=Mumbai}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |6,616.79<ref name=\"pmrda\"/>\n|\n|-\n|3