Pradesh]] and [[List of states and territories of India by area|third largest state by area]] in India. Maharashtra is the wealthiest state in India, contributing 15% of the country's industrial output and 13.3% of its GDP (2006\u20132007 figures).<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.worldbank.org.in/WBSITE/EXTERNAL/COUNTRIES/SOUTHASIAEXT/INDIAEXTN/0,,contentMDK:20951183~pagePK:141137~piPK:141127~theSitePK:295584,00.html | location = India | title = Countries | publisher = World Bank | date =  | accessdate = 2008-10-31 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120213182416/http://www.worldbank.org.in/WBSITE/EXTERNAL/COUNTRIES/SOUTHASIAEXT/INDIAEXTN/0,,contentMDK:20951183~pagePK:141137~piPK:141127~theSitePK:295584,00.html | archive-date = 13 February 2012 | url-status = dead }}</ref>\n\nMaharashtra is bordered in the [[Arabian Sea]] to the west, [[Gujarat]] and the [[Union territory]] of [[Dadra and Nagar Haveli]] to the northwest, [[Madhya Pradesh]] to the north and northeast, [[Chhattisgarh]] to the east, [[Karnataka]] to the south, [[Telangana]] to the southeast and [[Goa]] to the southwest. The state covers an area of {{convert|307731|km2|sqmi|0|abbr=on}} or 9.84% of the total geographical area of India. [[Mumbai]], the capital city of the state, is India's largest city and the financial capital of the nation. [[Nagpur]] is the second  capital of the state. [[Marathi language|Marathi]] is the state's official language.\n\nMaharashtra is the world's [[List of country subdivisions by population|second most populous first-level administrative country sub-division]]. Were it a nation in its own right, Maharashtra would be the [[List of countries by population|world's tenth most populous country]] ahead of [[Mexico]]. There are 41000 villages and 378 urban centres in Maharashtra.{{cn|date=April 2019}}\n\n==List of metropolitan areas in Maharashtra==\n\n{{See also|List of metropolitan areas in India}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n! clas